  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üíé Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nHi team,\r\n\r\nI am trying to recompute each validator rewards and penalities from your API (I use a node provider that expose your API). To do so, I need to convert `aggregation_bits` from `/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/{block_id}` into a bits sequence. When I do it in python, it seems that I don't match my benchmark [here](https://beaconcha.in/slot/201#attestations).\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nI request `/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/201` and I parse the response to get attestations. If I take the first attestation, the aggregation_bits is `0xf3fffd7b7ffeffffa79cffdffffffeaf1f` (attestation 0 for slot 200 for committee index 3). It's value in base 16 is `83028884456695686044921547418798697393951` and it bits representation is `1111001111111111111111010111101101111111111111101111111111111111101001111001110011111111110111111111111111111111111111101010111100011111` which doesn't match the sequence from the [benchmark](https://beaconcha.in/slot/201#attestations). I guess I missed something.\r\n\r\n**May you help me to understand what's wrong with my implementation ?**",
